'''''Bastien and Bastienne''''' is a 1963 Australian TV performance of the opera ''[[Bastien and Bastienne]]'' by [[Mozart]].
It was directed by Christopher Muir, who said, We will not be presenting the opera as it was originally performed. "We will be doing it in a style that will lend itself to TV, but we have, of course, treated the work with great respect to the young Mozart's original intention."<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article131724214 |title=TV AND RADIO HIGHLIGHTS |newspaper=[[The Canberra Times]] |volume=37, |issue=10,566 |location=Australian Capital Territory, Australia |date=19 June 1963 |accessdate=14 February 2017 |page=35 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref>
==Cast== *George Hegan as Bastien *Eunice McCowan as Bastienne *Janet Phillips *Patricia Gough *Roland Heimans
