{{Infobox person | name = Marie-Pierre Pruvot | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1935|11|11}} | birth_place = Isser, [[Kabylie]], [[Algeria]] | other_names = Bambi, Marie-Pier Ysser | known_for = | occupation = Entertainer, teacher, author }} '''Marie-Pierre Pruvot''' (also known under the pseudonym '''Marie-Pier Ysser''', 11 November 1935) is an [[Algeria]]n-born [[France|French]] [[transsexual]] woman who performed under the [[stage name]] '''Bambi'''.<ref name="Foerster">Foerster, Maxime (2006). ''Histoire des transsexuels en France'', H&O, {{ISBN|978-2845471382}}</ref> She performed in a transgender [[showgirl]] revue at [[Le Carrousel de Paris]] for approximately 20 years.<ref name="Dayan">Dayan, Josée (dir). (2008) ''[http://www.fipa.tm.fr/en/programs/2008/nous-n-irons-plus-au-bois-18280.htm Nous n'irons plus au bois.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120816231353/http://www.fipa.tm.fr/en/programs/2008/nous-n-irons-plus-au-bois-18280.htm |date=2012-08-16 }}'' [No More Hide and Seek] Passionfilms</ref>
While performing regularly, she appeared in several documentaries, including the 1959 film ''Costa Azzurra'', directed by [[Vittorio Sala]]<ref name="sala">Sala, Vittorio (dir.) (1959). ''[https://pro.imdb.com/title/tt0052704/ Costa Azzurra.]'' Glomer Film</ref> and the 1963 film ''90 notti in giro per il mondo'', directed by Mino Loy.<ref name="Loy">Loy, Mino (1963). ''[https://pro.imdb.com/title/tt0189334/ 90 notti in giro per il mondo.]'' Documento Film</ref> During her entertainment career, she acquired university degrees at the [[University of Paris|Sorbonne]] in Paris, subsequently becoming a teacher of literature in 1974. She was initially appointed in [[Cherbourg]]; two years later, she began teaching at [[Garges-lès-Gonesse]], and remained there for the next 25 years. She was honored with induction into the [[Ordre des Palmes Académiques]].<ref name="pruvot2007">Pruvot, Marie-Pierre (2007). ... j'ai changé de sexe. ''[[Paris Match]]''</ref>
She was profiled in [[Sébastien Lifshitz]]'s documentary film ''[[Bambi (2013 film)|Bambi]]'', which won the [[Teddy Award]] for Best Documentary Film at the [[2013 Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref name=teddyfamily>[http://www.interviewmagazine.com/film/teddy-award-berlinale#_ "Berlin's Teddy Family"]. ''[[Interview (magazine)|Interview]]'', March 2013.</ref>
