{{distinguish|Nibbler (video game)}} {{use mdy dates|date=February 2015}} {{Infobox video game | title = Nibblers | image = File:Nibblers_icon.jpg | caption = Game icon | developer = [[Rovio Entertainment]] | publisher = Rovio Entertainment | platforms = [[iOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]] | released = September 10, 2015 | genre = [[puzzle video game|Puzzle]] | modes = [[Single-player]] }}
'''''Nibblers''''' is a [[Mobile game|mobile]] [[tile-matching]] [[puzzle video game]], developed by [[Rovio Entertainment]]. It was released on September 10, 2015 for [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[iOS]] devices worldwide.
In the game, fish called "Nibblers" have wandered ashore to eat fruits, such as berries and melons. However, the lizards want to stop them. So, with the player's help, the Nibblers set on to defeat the lizards.
==Gameplay== Players match up three or more pieces of fruit. Matching three next to a lizard stuns it and then matching three more defeats it. Matching up four or more pieces summons Nibblers, as well as other sea creatures, that will attack lizards directly; a level ends when all lizards are defeated.<ref>[http://www.gamezebo.com/2015/05/01/rovio-soft-launches-nibblers-in-canada-a-game-of-primordial-match-3-fun/ Rovio Soft-launches ‘Nibblers’ in Canada, a Game of Primordial Match-3 Fun]. Retrieved 10 September 2015</ref>
==Reception== Android Authority gave the game a 7/10 because, although the game has cute graphics and can prove somewhat addictive, it has no special features that would set it apart from hundreds of other, similar 'match-3 games'. The reviewer also discussed not liking the fact that the life meter limits play due to taking 2.5 hours for each heart to regenerate - or else by paying actual money in order to overcome the waiting time.<ref>[http://www.androidauthority.com/nibblers-review-641535/ Nibblers Review] September 11, 2015. Retrieved October 20, 2015.</ref>
At the Finnish Game Music Awards 2016, Nibblers was awarded best game music; the soundtrack was composed by Salla Hakkola.<ref>[http://www.rovio.com/game-music-awards-2016-rovio-wins-best-game-music-nibblers GAME MUSIC AWARDS 2016: Rovio wins Best Game Music with Nibblers] Retrieved July 20, 2016.</ref>
