{{Infobox person | name = Yevgeny Petrosyan | honorific_suffix = [[People’s Artist of the RSFSR|PAR]] | image = Евгений Петросян .jpg | caption = At a meeting with Runet bloggers in October 2009. | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1945|9|16|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Baku]], [[USSR]] | death_date = | death_place = | medium = | nationality = Russian |years_active = 1962 – present | genre = | subject = | influences = | influenced = | spouse = [[Yelena Stepanenko]] | domesticpartner = | notable_work = | signature = | website = | footnotes = |title = [[People’s Artist of the RSFSR]] (1991) |awards = {{plainlist | * [[File:Orden of Honour.png|25px]] [[Order of Honour (Russia)|Order of Honour]] }} }}
'''Yevgeny Vaganovich Petrosyan''' ({{lang-ru|Евге́ний Вага́нович Петрося́н}}, {{lang-hy|Եվգենի Վահանի Պետրոսյան (Պետրոսյանց)}}; born on 16 September 1945 in [[Baku]], [[USSR]]) is a [[USSR|Soviet]]/[[Russia]]n comedian of [[Armenians|Armenian]] and [[Jewish]] descents.<ref>[http://alt.kp.ru/daily/24559.3/733507/ Евгений Петросян много шутил, но проиграл Интернету]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sem40.ru/famous2/m1516.shtml|title=Interview with Vladimir Vinokur|language=Russian|trans-title=Актеры и режиссеры - Знай Наших - Центральный Еврейский Ресурс|publisher=|accessdate=3 February 2016|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304120755/http://www.sem40.ru/famous2/m1516.shtml|archivedate=4 March 2016|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fhm.ru/?p=330|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120306042042/http://www.fhm.ru/?p=330|dead-url=yes|archive-date=6 March 2012|title=FHM RUSSIA - FHM.RU -|publisher=|accessdate=3 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sem40.ru/famous2/e1742.shtml|title=Yevgeny Petrosyan on sem40.ru|language=Russian|trans-title= Центральный Еврейский Ресурс. Сайт русскоязычных евреев всего мира. Еврейские новости. Еврейские фамилии.|publisher=|accessdate=3 February 2016}}</ref> He was named in 2005 among the most influential figures in contemporary Russia, in a survey conducted by independent polling agency The Levada Centre.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cdi.org/russia/johnson/9091-4.cfm|title=To Join the Elite, It's TV That Counts|publisher=Moscow Times|first=Nabi|last=Abdullaev|date=15 March 2005}}</ref> Popular since the days of the [[USSR]],<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=|year=1989|title=The New Yorker - Google Books|url=https://books.google.com/books?cd=7&id=Yf_jAAAAMAAJ&dq=%22Yevgeny+Petrosyan%22&q=petrosyan#search_anchor|journal=The New Yorker|volume=65|page=107|pages=|via=|number=11-19}}</ref> Petrosyan was the host of TV variety show ''Crooked Mirror''.<ref name="stp">{{Cite news|url=http://www.sptimes.ru/index.php?story_id=29618&action_id=2|publisher=St Petersburg Times|first=Anna|last=Malpas|title=Culture - In the Spotlight|date=14 August 2009}}</ref>
==Personal life==
Yevgeny is married to actress and humorist [[Yelena Stepanenko]] (born 1953)<ref name="peoples.ru">[http://www.peoples.ru/tv/petrosyan/history.html Четыре жены Евгения Петросяна]</ref>. Their engagement was in 1985. But Russian mass media announced on August 3, 2018 that Yevgeny and Yelena are getting divorced. They had made 1.5 billion rubles together while married. That money will now be divided among the two by the court of law.
