{{nihongo|'''Yokosuka Museum of Art'''|横須賀美術館|Yokosuka bijutsukan}} opened in {{nihongo|[[Kannonzaki Park]]|[[:ja:観音崎公園|観音崎公園]]}}, [[Yokosuka, Kanagawa|Yokosuka]], [[Kanagawa Prefecture]], Japan, in 2007. The collection, numbering some 5,000 pieces, includes works by [[Fujishima Takeji]] and [[Nakamura Tsune]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://bunka.nii.ac.jp/museums/detail/13805 |script-title=ja:横須賀美術館 |trans-title=Yokosuka Museum of Art |language=Japanese |publisher=[[Agency for Cultural Affairs]] |accessdate=14 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.yokosuka-moa.jp/collection/index.html |script-title=ja:収集方針 |trans-title=Collection Policy |language=Japanese |publisher=Yokosuka Museum of Art |accessdate=14 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.city.yokosuka.kanagawa.jp/8171/sisetu/fc10000878.html |script-title=ja:横須賀美術館 |trans-title=Yokosuka Museum of Art |language=Japanese |publisher=[[Yokosuka, Kanagawa|Yokosuka City]] |date=30 July 2015 |accessdate=14 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.yokosuka-moa.jp/collection/index.html |script-title=ja:所蔵作品 |trans-title=The Collection |language=Japanese |publisher=Yokosuka Museum of Art |accessdate=14 October 2015}}</ref>
